physical_examinations.vital_signs: Blood pressure: normal; Serum electrolytes: normal
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Micropenis, inguinal testes, underdeveloped scrotum noted at birth for Patient 1. Patient 2 had micropenis, chordee, scrotal hypospadias, and small testes (volume 0.5 ml) with an otherwise normal physical examination. Patient 4 evaluated for micropenis with chordee and undescended testes; testosterone was low [20 ng/dl (0.7 nmol/liter)].
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Patient 1 is now 21 years old, Tanner 5 with a 7-cm penis. Patient 2 is 14.6 years old, Tanner 2 with a 3-cm penis. Patient 3 is now 16.5 years old, Tanner 5 with an 8-cm penis.

physical_examinations.vital_signs: Testosterone: Patient 1 - 150 ng/dl (5.25 nmol/liter); Patient 2 - 100 ng/dl (3.5 nmol/liter)
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Elevated basal and post-ACTH 17OHP levels. Serum cortisol showed poor response to ACTH.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Two patients had high FSH levels indicating Sertoli cell failure. Patient 1 had FSH levels of 36.5 mIU/liter and LH levels of 14 mIU/liter at 21 years of age.
